Business Brief -- BankAmerica Corp.:
   California Attorney General
   Accepts Proposal for Merger
BankAmerica is based in San Francisco and Security Pacific
is based in Los Angeles. Their proposed merger was blessed
Feb. 28 by the U.S. Justice Department and the Attorney
General of Washington state, subject to divestiture of $8.8
billion of deposits, $2.7 billion in loans, and 211 branches
in five western states. Arizona's Attorney General approved
the deal Feb. 29 with no further spinoff requirements.
   The Federal Reserve Board must still sign off on the deal,
which is expected to close by the end of April.